    <section aria-labelledby="why-heading" class="intro">
        <h2 class="section-title" id="why-heading">Why Use Games for Stand-ups?</h2>
        <div class="intro__content">
            <p>Traditional stand-up meetings often become repetitive and dry. By introducing a small element of <strong>randomness and play</strong>, you can:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Improve Engagement:</strong> Team members pay more attention when the speaking order is unpredictable.</li>
                <li><strong>Foster Culture:</strong> A quick 30-second game creates shared moments of fun, even in remote teams.</li>
                <li><strong>Ensure Fairness:</strong> No one feels "picked on" when a turtle race or a pinball machine chooses the next speaker.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Customize player names and team branding in <a href="/apps/settings/">Settings</a>. Looking for more structured tools? Check our <a href="/agile/">Agile Planning Hub</a> for estimation and retrospectives, or explore our <a href="/randomizers/">Random Pickers &amp; Decision Tools</a>.</p>
